{"questionId":"22210164","questionHtml":"<p>Use <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;to determine an approximate value for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>.</p>\n<p>Give your answer in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>c</mi><mi>d</mi></mfrac></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>19</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>19</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>279</mn><mn>200</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;(or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>attempt to substitute&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;into&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mn>10</mn><msqrt><mn>48</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;(or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>10</mn><mrow><mn>4</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mo>≈</mo><mfrac><mn>279</mn><mn>200</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;(or equivalent in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>≈</mo><mfrac><mn>279</mn><mn>500</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>≈</mo><mfrac><mn>500</mn><mn>279</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22210164","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ2.12e","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Use x=110 to determine an approximate value for 3. Give your answer in the form cd, where c, d∈ℤ+.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.19—Maclaurin series"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}